Russian Equity Movers: Lukoil, Polymetal, Sberbank Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-05-31T15:18:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/russian-equity-movers-lukoil-polymetal-sberbank-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose 1.3
percent to 1,666.3 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The dollar-
denominated RTS Index added 1.2 percent to 1,888.60.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX),  Russia ’s second-biggest oil producer,
climbed the most since February, rising 3.8 percent to 1,819.5
rubles on the Micex. Crude for July delivery rose as much as
$2.17 to $102.77 a barrel.  OAO Polymetal (PMTL RX), a Russian silver producer, gained
to its strongest level in more than a month, adding 2.4 percent
to 540.7 rubles as silver futures advanced.  OAO Sberbank (SBER03 RX) advanced to its highest level
since May 16 after the Russian lender’s first-quarter profit
beat analysts’ estimates. The shares closed 0.3 percent higher
at 97.61 rubles, a sixth day of gains.  To contact the reporter on this story:
